Grease 9-inch cake pan and pre-heat oven to 350 degrees F. Open crescent roll and lay dough out flat on a cutting board. Dollop 1/2 cup of apple butter onto the dough and spread out evenly. Cut the dough into 1/2-inch strips. Roll each strip with the apple butter side in and place on its side in the pan. Bake for 18 minutes or until golden brown. Mix 1/2 cup of cream cheese icing with 2 Tablespoons of apple butter. Drizzle icing over warm rolls.